<HEAD>10 Most Expensive Paintings Sold At Christie's And Sotheby's</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Picasso</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Following is a current list of the top 10 prices paid for
paintings at the world's two major auction houses, Christie's and
Sotheby's:
   
   1. ``Irises'' by Vincent van Gogh; $53.90 million, sold by
Sotheby's, New York, Nov. 11, 1987.
   2. ``Sunflowers'' by van Gogh; $41.3 million, sold by Christie's,
London, March 31, 1987.
   3. ``Acrobat and Young Harlequin'' by Pablo Picasso; $38.46
million (record for a 20th-century work), sold by Christie's,
London, Nov. 28, 1988.
   4. ``Maternity'' by Picasso; $24.75 million, sold by Christie's,
New York, Nov. 14, 1988.
   5. ``In the Field'' by Claude Monet; $24.90 million, sold by
Sotheby's, London, June 28, 1988.
   6. ``The Trinquetalle Bridge'' by van Gogh; $20.24 million, sold
by Christie's, London, June 29, 1987.
   7. ``False Start'' by Jasper Johns; $17.05 million (record for a
living artist), sold by Sotheby's, New York, Nov. 10, 1988.
   8. ``Bird Cage'' by Picasso, $15.4 million, sold by Sotheby's,
New York, Nov. 10, 1988.
   9. ``Portrait of Adeline Ravoux'' by van Gogh; $13.75 million,
sold by Christie's, New York, May 11, 1988.
   10. ``The Railroad Bridge at Argenteuil,'' by Monet, $12.55
million, sold by Christie's, London, Nov. 28. 1988.
</TEXT>
